    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "In addition to setting up large databases containing component area, tentative compound identities, match factors, captured m/z values, retention time indices, sample identities, and the unique IDs, the function also communicates with online databases to download relevant information about every tentative compound... All this information, including the large databases, are stored as a list in a user-defined object.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper confirms that spreadOut() returns a list object containing component area, compound identities, match factors, m/z values, retention times, and downloaded information from online databases. However, the paper does not explicitly name the output object as 'standard_spread' nor does it enumerate the exact eight matrices and one nested list structure with the specific field names (Compounds, RT, MatchFactor, MZ, Mass, Area, rtBYmass, webInfo) as claimed in the card. The functional content matches but the specific structural naming and organization is not verified in the passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pone-0306202",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "structured R list object (standard_spread) containing eight nested matrices and one nested list: Compounds, RT, MatchFactor, MZ, Mass, Area, rtBYmass (RT|mass codes), and webInfo (published names, top m/z peaks, exact mass, and literature RTs per compound)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:24:45.041969+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card focuses specifically on the spreadOut() function and its output structure, which is appropriate to the paper's scope as spreadOut() is described as the first and foundational function in the uafR workflow.",
        "The expected output description is highly specific about field names and structure (e.g., 'standard_spread', 'rtBYmass') that are not explicitly confirmed in the provided passages, though the functional components are described."
      ],
