    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_003/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For the chemical structure processing, our package utilizes... The substructure information generated using ChemmineR includes the number of rings, all subgroups (e.g., R-COH, R-COOH, etc.) and their counts, all atoms (e.g., C, N, S, As, etc.) and their counts, and the number of charges for every chemical with published structural data (or canonical SMILES from CACTUS) on PubChem. This information is generated using the 'read.SDFset()' function from another R package called ChemmineR [33]. This package is a dependency that is installed with uafR and is core to the cheminformatics methods deployed.",
      "asbval:note": "ChemmineR is explicitly named as a dependency used for substructure analysis in the categorate() function.",
