    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/compound-structural-fingerprint-comparison/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For example, if a researcher has a set of plant chemicals of interest to test against active ingredients in pharmaceuticals, the input library could contain n columns whose headings are the biological activity (e.g., diuretic, blood pressure, etc.) and the contents (rows under the heading) are the active chemicals used in products that are approved for those medical outcomes. The 'categorate()' function will then take the input library (saved as a '.CSV') and compare every chemical of interest to the chemicals in each user-defined 'chemical category,' returning two additional data frames\u2014(1) whether it has a strong (Tanimoto similarity greater than 0.95) or moderate (greater than 0.85) structural match with any of the chemicals in each group",
      "asbval:note": "The use case of comparing query chemicals against a reference library organized by type/group is explicitly described.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pone-0306202",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "compound-structural-fingerprint-comparison",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Use this skill when you have a set of query chemicals and a reference library (organized by type or group), and you need to determine which reference compounds most closely resemble each query chemical based on structural features.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:29:45.962030+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/compound-structural-fingerprint-comparison/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "whether it has a strong (Tanimoto similarity greater than 0.95) or moderate (greater than 0.85) structural match",
      "asbval:note": "The paper confirms Tanimoto similarity thresholds (\u22650.95 for strong matches) but does not provide the specific example of ethyl hexanoate to isobutyl hexanoate matching. The example is illustrative but not validated in the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pone-0306202",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "compound-structural-fingerprint-comparison",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This is particularly important when validating that the categorate() function correctly identifies structural matches (e.g., matching ethyl hexanoate to isobutyl hexanoate with a similarity score \u22650.95)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
