      "asbval:note": "Match.Factor is explicitly named in passage 5 as a column in GC-MS output; passage 5 describes subsetting by 'minimal match factor' and passage 7 shows concrete examples of filtering at >65%, >75%, >88.9%, >97.2% thresholds.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pone-0306202",
