      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:31:38.351625+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/ms-peak-table-format-validation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "After reading the data into R and loading the package, uafR can use published information to sort and precisely select portions of the data that the user may be interested in. A diagram of the workflow can be seen in Fig 1. The first function for GC -MS data is \"spreadOut().\"\n\nRunning this function on properly formatted GC -MS input will automatically prepare the data for the next steps in the processing pipeline.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly states that spreadOut() is the first function and requires 'properly formatted GC-MS input', confirming that validation should occur before this function.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pone-0306202",
