    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/ms-peak-table-format-validation/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For the chemical structure processing, our package utilizes Tanimoto similarity, a commonly used and rigorously tested metric for physicochemical comparisons... The substructure information generated using ChemmineR includes the number of rings, all subgroups (e.g., R-COH, R-COOH, etc.) and their counts, all atoms (e.g., C, N, S, As, etc.) and their counts, and the number of charges for every chemical with published structural data (or canonical SMILES from CACTUS) on PubChem.",
      "asbval:note": "ChemmineR is used in the paper for substructure analysis via the 'read.SDFset()' function and is described as 'a dependency that is installed with uafR and is core to the cheminformatics methods deployed.' However, ChemmineR is not directly involved in peak table format validation\u2014it is used downstream in the categorate() function for structural analysis. The card's inclusion of ChemmineR as a tool for 'ms-peak-table-format-validation' is a scope misalignment; ChemmineR is used for chemical structure processing, not input schema validation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pone-0306202",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "ms-peak-table-format-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "ChemmineR (listed as a tool with evidence_spans mentioning 'uafR taps into an amazing set of cheminformatics packages -- ChemmineR, fmcsR, webchem')",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:31:38.351625+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/ms-peak-table-format-validation/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "It performs these comparisons using the \"fmcsBatch()\" function from the R package fmcsR [34].",
      "asbval:note": "fmcsR is used in the paper for structural similarity comparisons in the categorate() function, not for peak table format validation. The card's inclusion of fmcsR as a tool for 'ms-peak-table-format-validation' is a scope misalignment; fmcsR is used for chemical structure similarity matching downstream.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pone-0306202",
