      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/ms-peak-table-format-validation/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To collect these data, the function converts the chemical names into PubChem compound identifiers (CIDs) using the \"get_cid()\" function from the R package webchem [32].",
      "asbval:note": "webchem is used in the paper for converting chemical names to PubChem CIDs in the spreadOut() function, not for peak table format validation. The card's inclusion of webchem as a tool for 'ms-peak-table-format-validation' is a scope misalignment; webchem is used for chemical name normalization and database integration downstream.",
