        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-library-matching-validation/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "This information is generated using the 'read.SDFset()' function from another R package called ChemmineR [33]. This package is a dependency that is installed with uafR and is core to the cheminformatics methods deployed.",
      "asbval:note": "ChemmineR is confirmed as a dependency used for cheminformatics operations.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pone-0306202",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-library-matching-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "ChemmineR: underlying cheminformatics package for compound structure and property queries in enrichment workflows",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:33:06.634999+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-library-matching-validation/008",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To address these barriers in the use of GC-MS data, we developed an R package that takes the raw, aggregated chemical identifications generated from a user-selected peak detection software... The package here comes after the initial processing of samples and communicates with public chemistry utilities (including PubChem and the National Cancer Institute) to sort and process the aggregated set of all tentatively identified molecules",
      "asbval:note": "Scope aligns with paper's stated purpose.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pone-0306202",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-library-matching-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply this skill when you have GC-MS data preprocessed into a structured spread format and need to confirm that a set of known or suspected compounds are correctly identified in your samples.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:33:06.634999+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-library-matching-validation/009",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Another concern with manually selecting component areas for the same tentative molecule across different samples is the inherent subjectivity and inconsistency at many decision points... A package that automates the sorting and collection of component areas across samples in an experiment while simultaneously storing critical information about every tentative molecule could propel every field of science forward",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly addresses aggregation across samples and handling of inconsistencies.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pone-0306202",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-library-matching-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Use it after initial peak detection and compound assignment, particularly when match factors vary across replicates or when you need to aggregate fragmented peak calls for the same chemical across multiple sample files.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:33:06.634999+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-library-matching-validation/010",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The current build of uafR is optimized for raw output from Agilent's Unknowns Analysis Software (Santa Clara, CA, USA, 95051); however, the only aspect of the workflow that is specific to their software are the column names for the input data frame... a single '.CSV' file containing basic GC-MS output [i.e. retention times, peak area, captured mass-to-charge ratios (m/z), compound name, match quality]",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms strict column name requirements.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pone-0306202",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-library-matching-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Input data lacks strict column names (Component.RT, Component.Area, Base.Peak.MZ, File.Name, Compound.Name, Match.Factor) \u2014 preprocessing will fail.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:33:06.634999+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-library-matching-validation/011",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Instances where the chemical cannot be identified by name on PubChem (i.e. compounds for which a CID are unavailable) are redirected to CADD Group Chemoinformatics Tools and User Services (CACTUS, https://cactus.nci.nih.gov/)",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms that unmatched chemical names require fallback to CACTUS; if neither works, no match is returned.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pone-0306202",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-library-matching-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Query chemical names do not match published compound names in the spectral library \u2014 no matches will be returned.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:33:06.634999+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/structural-type-categorization/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The 'categorate()' function also uses PubChem to communicate with online databases and generate categorically, structurally, and chemically identifying information for every published chemical in the dataset... After the categorical information is collected, the function generates substructure data for the chemicals to also be subsetted by common functional groups. This information is generated using the 'read.SDFset()' function from another R package called ChemmineR. This package is a dependency that is installed with uafR and is core to the cheminformatics methods deployed... It performs these comparisons using the 'fmcsBatch()' function from the R package fmcsR.",
      "asbval:note": "All three tools (ChemmineR, fmcsR, webchem) are explicitly named and their roles in structural similarity matching and categorization are confirmed.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pone-0306202",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "structural-type-categorization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "A cheminformatics workflow that categorizes query chemicals against a reference library by computing structural similarity scores and identifying best-matched compounds in each library group. Uses ChemmineR, fmcsR, and webchem to enable structural matching and assessment across c",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:33:32.976906+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/structural-type-categorization/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "This information is generated using the 'read.SDFset()' function from another R package called ChemmineR [33]. This package is a dependency that is installed with uafR and is core to the cheminformatics methods deployed.",
      "asbval:note": "ChemmineR explicitly identified as core to cheminformatics methods in categorate().",
