      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "A simple and effective approach is to subset the search chemicals by setting a minimal match factor on the raw output of Unknowns Analysis (or other GC -MS software)... We found that uafR was able to identify the manually selected compounds with accurate matches to manually identified retention times (Table 1) and yielded the same overall pattern of significance in ANOSIM analysis (Table 2).",
      "asbval:note": "The paper demonstrates this exact use case: comparing compound retention and statistical outcomes across multiple Match.Factor thresholds to select optimal filtering criteria.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pone-0306202",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
